<ul>
<li><a href="http://politics.guardian.co.uk/columnist/story/0,9321,1293144,00.html" class="external text" title="http://politics.guardian.co.uk/columnist/story/0,9321,1293144,00.html" rel="nofollow">Politically correct and proud of it Observer Special Report by Will Hutton</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.linguistlist.org/issues/7/7-879.html" class="external text" title="http://www.linguistlist.org/issues/7/7-879.html" rel="nofollow">Possible origins of the term at www.linguist.org</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.languagemonitor.com/politically_correct/" class="external text" title="http://www.languagemonitor.com/politically_correct/" rel="nofollow">Global Language Monitor list of the Top Ten Politically (In)Correct Terms from 2007 back to 2005</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.lrb.co.uk/v27/n23/print/jone01_.html" class="external text" title="http://www.lrb.co.uk/v27/n23/print/jone01_.html" rel="nofollow">"Shortcuts"</a> by Thomas Jones, discusses the term "political correctness" in British discourse, <i><a href="/wiki/London_Review_of_Books" title="London Review of Books">London Review of Books</a></i>, December 1, 2005</li>
<li><a href="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/pages/live/articles/news/news.html?in_article_id=420729&amp;in_page_id=1770" class="external text" title="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/pages/live/articles/news/news.html?in_article_id=420729&amp;in_page_id=1770" rel="nofollow">A list of examples cited by the Daily Mail of political correctness in the UK</a></li>
</ul>


